#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:27
#: d3d3ecb19cf043bd82334de8f85d8ba8
msgid "Keyboard layout settings not behaving correctly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:30
#: b157961950bf4cdd95b59362eb0b93db
msgid ""
"The best approach is to choose the right keyboard layout during the "
"installation process. But if you want to change things afterwards, you can "
"try this workaround."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:32
#: 0ea928e6bdca4a41ab6add51e2347834
msgid ""
"Assuming XFCE desktop: in ``Q`` → ``System Tools`` → ``Keyboard`` → "
"``Layout``, leave the checkbox “ ``Use system defaults``” checked. Do not "
"customize the keyboard layout here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:34
#: 99f406c6a2c548d894e10e1f10f11fe5
msgid ""
"Set the system-wide layout and options for ``xorg`` with the ``localectl`` "
"command in ``dom0``. You can use ``localectl --help`` as a starting point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:36
#: fd10b09221744acbbcee9bd32ae62721
msgid "Example: ``localectl set-x11-keymap us dell ,qwerty compose:caps``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:38
#: e01a4d24da76465eb7d9c64eb44ffc22
msgid ""
"This generates the appropriate configuration in "
"``/etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/00-keyboard.conf``. This file is auto-generated. Do "
"not edit it by hand, unless you know what you are doing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/hardware-troubleshooting.rst:40
#: 0f422aaee84d4dfaa1e308488b7597eb
msgid ""
"Restarting ``xorg`` is required. The most straightforward way is to reboot "
"the system."
msgstr ""

